review_blob: Bottled. pours out dark brown with a slight tan tint. Taste is great, matly, chocolate, coffee with a complex aftertaste combining characteristics of chocolate and coffee.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Reserve Cherry Oak Doppelbock

review_blob: Very good IPA and nice balance of hops. Pours a nice orange color. The aroma is standard IPA like: Pine. Taste is very nice with a slight bitterness.
Bud Light What?? Oh, Wheat! Sure...The aroma is nice. Smells a little like shock top. Taste is not too bad, I have had worse, but hey this is a light beer flavored with wheat and some orange peel.
